---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section class="landing">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">Enterprise AI Governance</p>
    <h1>Deterministic governance for AI runtime operations</h1>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      BeaconGuard is a runtime control plane that sits between enterprise applications and AI/model endpoints.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Explore platform fit</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/design-partner-program">Start design partner process</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Why BeaconGuard Exists</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprise AI systems often fail the same question under pressure:
      when outcomes need to be explained months later, what exactly was authorized,
      who decided it, and what evidence remains?
    </p>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard exists where application-level logs are not enough.
      It brings authorization intent and enforcement outcomes into a durable, deterministic boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>What BeaconGuard Does</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard operates as an externalized control plane that sits between
      enterprise systems and AI endpoints.
    </p>
    <p>Authorization logic is enforced centrally, then returned to applications as an explicit decision with context.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Where BeaconGuard Sits</h2>
    <div class="flow-diagram flow-diagram--stack">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Application</p>
        <p>Produces request context and intent</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">BeaconGuard</p>
        <p>Evaluates policy and decides allow/deny</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">AI / Model Endpoint</p>
        <p>Executes only approved actions</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      Every request passes through this boundary before any model response can influence your workflow.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Core Platform Outcomes</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--compact">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Deterministic Control</h3>
        <p>The same input and policy context produce the same authorization outcome every time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Operational Governance</h3>
        <p>Governance logic is centralized, reducing drift in operational controls.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Evidence for Review</h3>
        <p>Decision context and outcomes are emitted for audit and incident review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Replayable Decisions</h3>
        <p>Equivalent inputs and policy state produce equivalent outcomes for reproducible review.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Decision and Evidence Flow</h2>
    <div class="flow-diagram flow-diagram--tight">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Request</p>
        <p>Policy context enters</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Decision</p>
        <p>Deterministic allow/deny with rationale</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Review Record</p>
        <p>Action, decision, and evidence stored</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard keeps model quality concerns separate from policy governance while preserving a review trail your assurance teams can rely on.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
    <p>Organizations running AI in production where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>authorization outcomes must be explainable and repeatable,</li>
      <li>decision evidence must be reviewable after the fact, and</li>
      <li>governance must be enforced independent of prompt or model implementation.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Design Partner Positioning</h2>
    <div class="stack-callout">
      <p>Design partners help us validate policy boundaries and evidence requirements before broad rollout.</p>
      <p><a href="/design-partner-program">Learn how we run design partner evaluations</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Get Started</h2>
    <p>
      Begin with platform fit, then progress to operational architecture and deployment posture.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Review the platform scope</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Talk to BeaconGuard</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>